<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I made a simple Bash script using Gum to quickly open dotfiles. Maybe some of you find it useful as well:</p> <p><a href="https://i.redd.it/piu51y6ojhe91.gif">https://i.redd.it/piu51y6ojhe91.gif</a></p> <p>The script can be configured to match your dot file folder path (~/.config by default), as well as which file types should be included. Also, there is an option to ignore git ignored files.</p> <p>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/AlexW00/dot-launcher">https://github.com/AlexW00/dot-launcher</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Rate-Worth"> /u/Rate-Worth </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/wb1d4k/dotlauncher_quickly_open_and_edit_dotfiles/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/wb1d4k/dotlauncher_quickly_open_and_edit_dotfiles/">[comments]</a></span>